This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for generating sentiment lexicons, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also deals with social media data, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for sentiment analysis, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves cross-lingual NLP, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing).
